    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import DatasetGenerator  # assuming your module is named DatasetGenerator.py\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a single dataset entry using the new parameter list:\n",
    "entry = DatasetGenerator.create_dataset_entry(\n",
    "    num_points_range=(3, 10),         # Range for number of control points per 2D curve\n",
    "    plane_width_range=(20, 100),       # 2D plane width range (fixed value here as a range with equal bounds)\n",
    "    plane_height_range=(20, 60),        # 2D plane height range (fixed value here)\n",
    "    num_samples=35,                   # Number of samples along the curves for interpolation\n",
    "    num_v=35,                          # Number of interpolation steps between curves\n",
    "    noise_std=0.15,                    # Standard deviation for added Gaussian noise\n",
    "    noise_mean=0.15,                    # Mean for the added noise\n",
    "    degree_u=3,                        # Degree in the u-direction for the NURBS surface\n",
    "    degree_v=3,                        # Degree in the v-direction for the NURBS surface\n",
    "    ctrlpts_size_u_range=(4, 8),         # Range for the number of control points in the u-direction\n",
    "    ctrlpts_size_v_range=(4, 8),         # Range for the number of control points in the v-direction\n",
    "    z_gap_range=(20, 100),              # Range from which to randomly pick the z-gap between curves\n",
    "    bspline_degree=3,                  # Degree used for creating the B-spline curves (typically cubic)\n",
    "    extrapolate=False,                 # Whether or not to allow B-spline extrapolation\n",
    "    random_rotation=True,\n",
    "    normalise=False,\n",
    "    show_visu=True                     # Enable visualization of intermediate steps\n",

   "source": [
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.utils import register_keras_serializable\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "#  helper: channel-wise Laplacian \n",
    "def laplacian(grid):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    grid : (B, H, W, C) tensor  C = 3 for (x,y,z)\n",
    "    returns channel-wise 4-neighbour Laplacian with SAME shape.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    lap_k = tf.constant([[0, 1, 0],\n",
    "                         [1, -4, 1],\n",
    "                         [0, 1, 0]], tf.float32)  # (3,3)\n",
    "    lap_k = lap_k[..., tf.newaxis, tf.newaxis]  # (3,3,1,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    C = tf.shape(grid)[-1]  # channel count at run-time\n",
    "    lap_k = tf.tile(lap_k, [1, 1, C, 1])  # (3,3,C,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return tf.nn.depthwise_conv2d(grid, lap_k,\n",
    "                                  strides=[1, 1, 1, 1],\n",
    "                                  padding='SAME')  # (B,H,W,C)\n",
    "# \n",
    "@register_keras_serializable(package='CustomLosses', name='total_loss')\n",
    "def total_loss(y_true, y_pred, w_lap=0.05):\n",
    "    mse = tf.reduce_mean(tf.square(y_true - y_pred))\n",
    "    lap = tf.reduce_mean(tf.square(laplacian(y_true) - laplacian(y_pred)))\n",
    "    return mse + w_lap * lap\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "dataset_file = \"dataset/dataset_10_surfaces_noise0.0_2109_1704.pkl\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "import os\n",
    "os.environ[\"CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES\"] = \"3\"\n",
    "# Import necessary packages and the compare library\n",
    "import pickle\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import surface_compare\n",
    "import tensorflow as tf\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load a sample dataset entry (assumed to be saved as a pickle file)\n",
    "# Replace 'sample_entry.pkl' with your actual dataset entry file path.\n",
    "\n",
    "# Import the non-visualization and visualization libraries\n",
    "import DatasetGenerator\n",
    "import nurbs_vis\n",
    "import pickle\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "#entry2 = entry\n",
    "# Load the dataset from file.\n",
    "with open(dataset_file, \"rb\") as f:\n",
    "    entry2 = pickle.load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load the trained model from the provided file.\n",
    "model = tf.keras.models.load_model(\"models/pointnet_surface_20250618_1830_100ep.keras\",\n",
    "                   custom_objects={'total_loss': total_loss})\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",

    "predicted_ctrl_net = model.predict(points)\n",
